title: Hello world
content: A "Hello, World!" program is traditionally used to introduce novice programmers to a programming language. "Hello, World!" is also traditionally used in a sanity test to make sure that a computer language is correctly installed, and that the operator understands how to use it. "Time to hello world" (TTHW) is a metric for the time to author a "Hello World" program in a given programming language and run it. History: "Hello, World!" program by Brian Kernighan (1978) While small test programs have existed since the development of programmable computers, the tradition of using the phrase "Hello World!" as a test message was influenced by an example program in the seminal 1978 book The C Programming Language [4] The example program in that book prints "hello, world", and was inherited from a 1974 Bell Laboratories internal memorandum by Brian Kernighan, Programming in C: A Tutorial:[5] - Wikipedia

title: Introduction to SQL
content: SQL is a database computer language designed for the retrieval and management of data in a relational database. SQL stands for Structured Query Language. This tutorial will give you a quick start to SQL. It covers most of the topics required for a basic understanding of SQL and to get a feel of how it works.SQL is Structured Query Language, which is a computer language for storing, manipulating and retrieving data stored in a relational database. SQL is the standard language for Relational Database System. All the Relational Database Management Systems (RDMS) like MySQL, MS Access, Oracle, Sybase, Informix, Postgres and SQL Server use SQL as their standard database language.

title: OOP Advance
content: As its name suggests, Object-Oriented Programming, or OOP, refers to programming languages that use objects in programming. Object-Oriented Programming aims to implement entities in the real world, such as inheritance, encapsulation, polymorphism, etc., in programming. The primary purpose of OOP is to link data and functions operating on them together so that no other part of the code can access this data except for that function.

title: The Programming School
content: A programming school serves as an invaluable gateway for individuals eager to embark on a journey into the dynamic world of software development. At its core, such an institution acts as a nurturing ground, providing aspiring programmers with the essential knowledge, skills, and guidance needed to thrive in this ever-evolving field. Through a combination of structured curriculum, hands-on projects, and mentorship, programming schools cultivate a supportive learning environment where students can explore various programming languages, paradigms, and tools. These schools often emphasize problem-solving abilities, critical thinking, and collaboration, empowering students to tackle real-world challenges with confidence. Additionally, programming schools often foster a vibrant community of learners, where students can network, collaborate on projects, and exchange ideas, further enriching their educational experience. Ultimately, a programming school equips its graduates with not just technical proficiency but also a mindset of continuous learning and adaptability, essential traits for success in the fast-paced world of software development.
